CI workflow that publishes the visualization site to GitHub Pages. Triggers on push to `main` and via manual `workflow_dispatch`.

The `build` job runs `cargo run --bin viz-data` to regenerate `out/viz-data.json`, then assembles a `_site` directory with `viz/index.html` at `_site/viz/index.html` and the generated JSON at `_site/out/viz-data.json`, and uploads it as a Pages artifact. The `deploy` job (depends on `build`) publishes that artifact via `actions/deploy-pages@v4`.

Coupling: assumes a binary target named `viz-data` exists in the Rust workspace that writes to `out/viz-data.json`, and that `viz/index.html` (client-side viz page) fetches data from a relative `../out/viz-data.json` path matching this layout — if either the binary name, its output path, or `viz/index.html`'s fetch path changes, this workflow (or the page) breaks silently. Uses `rustup show` to install the toolchain pinned by the repo's `rust-toolchain`/`rust-toolchain.toml` file rather than specifying a version inline. Concurrency group `pages` with `cancel-in-progress: false` ensures deploys queue rather than overlap or get cancelled mid-flight.